a poem of missing someone why do i continue to count the days torturing myself pretending to live painfully earnestly how many ways i'm only a man with but one life to give she stands and she smiles miles away i feel her ardor thoughtful and sincere off of the calendar just one more day when i think of her pain just gets severe i love her and i need her my wife to be how will i survive it three very long years but if you knew her i'm ecstatic you see three long years and over one million tears beautifully sad and sick in love with denial acceptance i'm truly sorry for your pain you should check out some of my poems please i love you your poems Jon Secada Eastern Orthodox Church Darth Vader Narcissism Time Out of Mind About Schmidt 613 mitzvot Kodocha Year of the Spider Teresa of Avila Past teachings of Prem Rawat Spike (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) Torture Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity Vladimir Nabokov Philipp Melanchthon Shaggy dog story Kurt Cobain Scenes from a Memory Poetry King James Version of the Bible Fitz Hugh Ludlow Darken Rahl The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Sin City Italian literature William Blake Mojave people Mortification of the flesh The Princess Bride The McGuire Sisters Sigmund Freud Darwin from Insectivorous plants to Worms Julian calendar Carrie Jacobs-Bond Humphrey Bogart Le Malade imaginaire Four Quartets Flagellation Hall & Oates Muslim ibn Aqeel James Russell Lowell Ten Commandments Duties of the Heart Grief Saudade Olivier Messiaen Yoga Sutras of Patanjali John the Baptist Kate Bush Marilyn Monroe Cliff Richard Meaning of life Sant Mat 2004 Republican National Convention Gregorian calendar 2005 Kashmir earthquake Hell Statius Fruits Basket Myles Standish Seppuku YuYu Hakusho The Catcher in the Rye Blaise Pascal Computus Jewish holiday Religious views of suicide Dean Koontz Adam Mickiewicz Billboard Hot 100 Storm (comics) Charlie Brown Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Nostradamus Jacques-Louis David A Co